					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, it has room for improvement. Apparently Nestopia 1.25 has a bug that causes the dot crawl pattern to be wrong (alternate between two patterns every other line, rather than cycle between <em>three</em>). It also crops to 640 for other reasons, cutting off active NES pixels.
<br />
<br />As for sharpness and specifics to the algorithm, I want to improve that and am slowly reading up on NTSC video modulation and have a desire to obtain an oscilloscope so I can find the exact NES composite video encoding scheme. Regarding how visible the dot crawl is, this is partly due to the quality of your display's chroma filter (comb filter). Currently this emulates a TV with no filter, resulting in very visible artifacts.</div>

